<Dashboard title="Docs: Export" activeNav="docs">
  <div class="max-w-3xl space-y-4">
    <p class="text-gray-700">
      Export produces a Shopify theme ZIP from the current project state.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm border border-gray-200 p-6">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">How it works</h2>
      <div class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <p>Files are generated based on the projectâ€™s chosen sections/blocks and saved settings.</p>
        <p>The ZIP is created using <code class="px-1 py-0.5 bg-gray-100 rounded">fflate</code> so it works in the Workers runtime.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm border border-gray-200 p-6">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Best practices</h2>
      <div class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <p>Validate the exported theme structure (required folders/files) before offering a download.</p>
        <p>Keep exports deterministic for easier diffs and debugging.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Dashboard>
